<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c220_11"> 
<div id="v220.11.1"><span class="H6030 s">Then answered</span><span class="H6691 s"> Zophar</span><span class="H5284 s"> the Naamathite</span><span class="H559 s">, and said</span>,</div> 
<div id="v220.11.2"><span class="H7230 s">Should not the multitude</span><span class="H1697 s"> of words</span><span class="H6030 s"> be answered</span><span class="H376 s">? and should a man</span><span class="H8193 s"> full of talk</span><span class="H6663 s"> be justified</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (full…: Heb. of lips)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.3"><span class="H907 s">Should thy lies</span><span class="H2790 s"> make</span><span class="H4962 s"> men</span><span class="H2790 s"> hold their peace</span><span class="H3932 s">? and when thou mockest</span><span class="H3637 s">, shall no man make thee ashamed</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (lies: or, devices)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.4"><span class="H559 s">For thou hast said</span><span class="H3948 s">, My doctrine</span><span class="H2134 s"> <i>is</i> pure</span><span class="H1249 s">, and I am clean</span><span class="H5869 s"> in thine eyes</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.11.5"><span class="H199 s">But</span><span class="H5414 s"> oh that</span><span class="H433 s"> God</span><span class="H1696 s"> would speak</span><span class="H6605 s">, and open</span><span class="H8193 s"> his lips</span> against thee;</div> 
<div id="v220.11.6"><span class="H5046 s">And that he would shew</span><span class="H8587 s"> thee the secrets</span><span class="H2451 s"> of wisdom</span><span class="H3718 s">, that <i>they are</i> double</span><span class="H8454 s"> to that which is</span><span class="H3045 s">! Know</span><span class="H433 s"> therefore that God</span><span class="H5382 s"> exacteth</span><span class="H5771 s"> of thee <i>less</i> than thine iniquity</span> <i>deserveth</i>.</div> 
<div id="v220.11.7"><span class="H2714 s">Canst thou by searching</span><span class="H4672 s"> find out</span><span class="H433 s"> God</span><span class="H4672 s">? canst thou find</span><span class="H7706 s"> out the Almighty</span><span class="H8503 s"> unto perfection</span>?</div> 
<div id="v220.11.8"><span class="H1363 s"><i>It is</i> as high</span><span class="H8064 s"> as heaven</span><span class="H6466 s">; what canst thou do</span><span class="H6013 s">? deeper</span><span class="H7585 s"> than hell</span><span class="H3045 s">; what canst thou know</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (as high…: Heb. the heights of heaven)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.9"><span class="H4055 s">The measure</span><span class="H752 s"> thereof <i>is</i> longer</span><span class="H776 s"> than the earth</span><span class="H7342 s">, and broader</span><span class="H3220 s"> than the sea</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.11.10"><span class="H2498 s">If he cut off</span><span class="H5462 s">, and shut up</span><span class="H6950 s">, or gather together</span><span class="H7725 s">, then who can hinder</span> him? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (cut…: or, make a change) (hinder…: Heb. turn him away?)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.11"><span class="H3045 s">For he knoweth</span><span class="H7723 s"> vain</span><span class="H4962 s"> men</span><span class="H7200 s">: he seeth</span><span class="H205 s"> wickedness</span><span class="H995 s"> also; will he not then consider</span> <i>it</i>?</div> 
<div id="v220.11.12"><span class="H5014 s">For vain</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H3823 s"> would be wise</span><span class="H120 s">, though man</span><span class="H3205 s"> be born</span><span class="H6501 s"> <i>like</i> a wild ass's</span><span class="H5895 s"> colt</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (vain: Heb. empty)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.13"><span class="H3559 s">If thou prepare</span><span class="H3820 s"> thine heart</span><span class="H6566 s">, and stretch</span><span class="H3709 s"> out thine hands</span> toward him;</div> 
<div id="v220.11.14"><span class="H205 s">If iniquity</span><span class="H3027 s"> <i>be</i> in thine hand</span><span class="H7368 s">, put it far away</span><span class="H5766 s">, and let not wickedness</span><span class="H7931 s"> dwell</span><span class="H168 s"> in thy tabernacles</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.11.15"><span class="H5375 s">For then shalt thou lift up</span><span class="H6440 s"> thy face</span><span class="H3971 s"> without spot</span><span class="H3332 s">; yea, thou shalt be stedfast</span><span class="H3372 s">, and shalt not fear</span>:</div> 
<div id="v220.11.16"><span class="H7911 s">Because thou shalt forget</span><span class="H5999 s"> <i>thy</i> misery</span><span class="H2142 s">, <i>and</i> remember</span><span class="H4325 s"> <i>it</i> as waters</span><span class="H5674 s"> <i>that</i> pass away</span>:</div> 
<div id="v220.11.17"><span class="H2465 s">And <i>thine</i> age</span><span class="H6965 s"> shall be clearer</span><span class="H6672 s"> than the noonday</span><span class="H5774 s">; thou shalt shine forth</span><span class="H1242 s">, thou shalt be as the morning</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (be clearer…: Heb. shall arise above the noon-day)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.18"><span class="H982 s">And thou shalt be secure</span><span class="H3426 s">, because there is</span><span class="H8615 s"> hope</span><span class="H2658 s">; yea, thou shalt dig</span><span class="H7901 s"> <i>about thee, and</i> thou shalt take thy rest</span><span class="H983 s"> in safety</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.11.19"><span class="H7257 s">Also thou shalt lie down</span><span class="H2729 s">, and none shall make <i>thee</i> afraid</span><span class="H7227 s">; yea, many</span><span class="H2470 s"> shall make suit</span><span class="H6440 s"> unto thee</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (make suit…: Heb. intreat thy face)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.11.20"><span class="H5869 s">But the eyes</span><span class="H7563 s"> of the wicked</span><span class="H3615 s"> shall fail</span><span class="H6 s">, and they shall not escape</span><span class="H4498 s"> †</span><span class="H8615 s">, and their hope</span><span class="H4646 s"> <i>shall be as</i> the giving up</span><span class="H5315 s"> of the ghost</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (they shall…: Heb. flight shall perish from them) (the giving…: or, a puff of breath)</span></div></div>

